primary_outcome.description:
Functional change in Harris Hip Score (HHS) from preoperative (baseline) to 3 years after surgery.
The maximum score of HHS is 100 points. Pain domain contributes 44 points, function 47, ROM 5 and absence of deformity 4 points.
Results can be interpreted with the following: Less than 60= failed result; 60 to 69= poor result; 70 to 79= fair; 80 to 90= good; 90 to 100= excellent;
